This needs better examples.  I find:<p><pre><code>  v4si multiply_four(v4si a, v4si b) { return a*b; }
</code></pre>
Much more readable, and just as portable.  There&#x27;s a typedef for v4si, of course, but you do that exactly once and then ignore it.  The IR produced is identical, and therefore just as portable.
